Iraq has set targets to reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions by 14% below business-as-usual (BAU) emissions by 2035. Of the 90 million metric tons of CO2 equivalent, 1% will be conditional and an additional 13% will be achieved through the unconditional target.
